#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
#. VAR: Bhojanavagga → dutiya­pavāra­ṇa­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 36"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:0.5"
msgid "36. Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "The second training rule on satisfaction"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.84, pts-cs-bu-pc36.1, pts-vp-en.2.332, ms2V_784
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr "At that time two monks were traveling on a main road through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.3"
msgid "Eko bhikkhu anācāraṃ ācarati."
msgstr "One monk misbehaved,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.4"
msgid "Dutiyo bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and the second monk said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.5"
msgid "“māvuso, evarūpamakāsi, netaṃ kappatī”ti."
msgstr "“Don’t do that; it’s not allowable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.6"
msgid "So tasmiṃ upanandhi."
msgstr "Because of that the first monk became resentful."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr "They then carried on to Sāvatthī."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.8"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṃghabhattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.9"
msgid "Dutiyo bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito hoti."
msgstr "When the second monk had eaten and expressed his satisfaction,"

#. VAR: Upanaddho → upanandho (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.10"
msgid "Upanaddho bhikkhu ñātikulaṃ gantvā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "the resentful monk went to his family and got some almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.11"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then went to the other and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.12"
msgid "“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Please eat!”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.13"
msgid "“Alaṃ, āvuso, paripuṇṇomhī”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no need; I’m full.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.14"
msgid "“Sundaro, āvuso, piṇḍapāto, bhuñjāhī”ti."
msgstr "“The almsfood is nice, please eat.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.15"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tena bhikkhunā nippīḷiyamāno taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñji."
msgstr "And because he was pressured, he ate the almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.16"
msgid "Upanaddho bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The resentful  monk then said to him,"

#. VAR: tvampi → tvaṃ hi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.17"
msgid "“tvampi nāma, āvuso, maṃ vattabbaṃ maññasi yaṃ tvaṃ bhuttāvī pavārito anatirittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti."
msgstr "“Who are you to correct me when you eat food that’s not leftover after having finished your meal and expressed your satisfaction?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: That is, why did he not say that the food was not leftover.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.18"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, ācikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have told me?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.19"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, pucchitabban”ti."
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have asked?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_785
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.20"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "The second monk told the monks what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.21"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.22"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized the other monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.23"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can a monk invite another monk who has finished eating and who has expressed his satisfaction to eat food that’s not leftover?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.24"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāresī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.333
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.25"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.26"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.27"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you invite another monk who has finished eating and who has expressed his satisfaction to eat food that’s not leftover?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.28"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.29"
msgid "evañca pana bhikkhave imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_786
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:1.30"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya—‘handa, bhikkhu, khāda vā bhuñja vā’ti, jānaṃ āsādanāpekkho, bhuttasmiṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk invites another monk, whom he knows has eaten and expressed his satisfaction, to eats staple or non-staple food which is not left over, saying, “Here, monk, eat,” aiming to criticize him, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc36.2.1, ms2V_787
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_788
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_789
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhuttāvī nāma"
msgstr "Who has eaten:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.9"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ, antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr "who has eaten any of the five staple foods, even just what fits on the tip of a blade of grass."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_790
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.10"
msgid "Pavārito nāma"
msgstr "Expressed his satisfaction:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.11"
msgid "asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati."
msgstr "there is eating; there is staple food; it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach; there is a refusal."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_791
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.12"
msgid "Anatirittaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not left over:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">_Akappiyakataṃ hoti_, literally, “It is done with what is not allowable.” The “it,” both here and below, refers to the ceremony of making it allowable, and the “what” refers to the food.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.13"
msgid "akappiyakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "the making it leftover is done with food that is not allowable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.14"
msgid "appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that has not been received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.15"
msgid "anuccāritakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that is not held in hand;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.16"
msgid "ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.17"
msgid "abhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has not finished eating;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.18"
msgid "bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā vuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has finished eating, who has expressed his satisfaction, but who has risen from his seat;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.19"
msgid "“alametaṃ sabban”ti avuttaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "“I’ve had enough of all of this,” has not been said;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.20"
msgid "na gilānātirittaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "it is not leftover from one who is sick—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.21"
msgid "etaṃ anatirittaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “not leftover.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_792
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.22"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.23"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the five staple foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_793
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.24"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple foods:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.25"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.26"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_794
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.27"
msgid "Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti"
msgstr "Invites:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.28"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti."
msgstr "saying, “Take as much as you like.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_795
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.29"
msgid "Jānāti nāma"
msgstr "He knows:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
# NOTE: The last of these three ways of knowing presumably refers to the other monk having told him directly. See discussion in note to Relinquishment 30, [](MS.1.2425).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.30"
msgid "sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti."
msgstr "he knows by himself or others have told him or the monk has told him."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_796
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.31"
msgid "Āsādanāpekkhoti"
msgstr "Aiming to criticize him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.32"
msgid "“iminā imaṃ codessāmi sāressāmi paṭicodessāmi paṭisāressāmi maṅkuṃ karissāmī”ti abhiharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he offers it to him, thinking, “With this I’ll accuse him/remind him/counter-accuse him/counter-remind him/humiliate him,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.334
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.33"
msgid "Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.34"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.1.35"
msgid "Bhojanapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When the other monk has finished eating, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, pts-vp-pli4.85, pts-cs-bu-pc36.2.2, ms2V_797
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.1"
msgid "Pavārite pavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, and he perceives that he has, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not leftover, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.2"
msgid "Pavārite vematiko anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, but he is unsure if he has, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not leftover, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.3"
msgid "Pavārite appavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, anāpatti."
msgstr "If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, but he perceives that he has not, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not leftover, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.4"
msgid "Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya abhiharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he invites him to eat post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.5"
msgid "Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.6"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.7"
msgid "Appavārite pavāritasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction,  but he perceives that he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.8"
msgid "Appavārite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.2.9"
msgid "Appavārite appavāritasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction, and he perceives that he has not, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-cs-bu-pc36.2.3, ms2V_798
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.2"
msgid "atirittaṃ kārāpetvā deti,"
msgstr "if he gives it after getting it made leftover;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.3"
msgid "“atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjāhī”ti deti,"
msgstr "if he gives it, saying, “Get it made leftover and then eat it;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.4"
msgid "aññassatthāya haranto gacchāhīti deti,"
msgstr "if he gives it, saying, “Take this food for the benefit of someone else;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.5"
msgid "gilānassa sesakaṃ deti,"
msgstr "if he gives the leftovers from a sick person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.6"
msgid "“yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjā”ti deti,"
msgstr "if he gives, saying, “When there’s a reason, make use of these post-midday tonics/seven-day tonics/lifetime tonics;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. VAR: Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ → dutiya­pavāra­ṇa­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_799
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:2.3.9"
msgid "Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the second training rule on satisfaction, is finished."
